abstract: Commerce Dept reports new orders for capital goods fell 0.4 percent in November, compared to downwardly-revised gain of 0.6 percent in October; says annual rate of new private homes sold in November rose 4.3 percent to seasonally adjusted rate of 490,000 units.
lead_paragraph: Though manufacturing measures were tepid, consumer sentiment is at a five-month high in December.

headline.main: Capital Goods Orders Fall, but Consumer Data Points Are Encouraging
headline.print_headline: Capital Goods Orders Fall, but Consumer Data Points Are Solid

snippet: Though manufacturing measures were tepid, consumer sentiment is at a five-month high in December.
